So the preparation for the
MoMA show, it's going well.

00:00:23.160 --> 00:00:25.466
I mean, it's a very big task for me

00:00:25.466 --> 00:00:26.851
because it's not just third perspective

00:00:26.851 --> 00:00:27.929
of my performers' work,

00:00:27.929 --> 00:00:31.978
it's what really stands for
some kind of historical view,

00:00:31.978 --> 00:00:33.346
what performers can be,

00:00:33.346 --> 00:00:35.182
and how the performers
can enter the museum,

00:00:35.182 --> 00:00:37.875
and how can be performers
collected from the museum,

00:00:37.875 --> 00:00:41.028
and what happen if a performer die,

00:00:41.028 --> 00:00:43.529
if the work can be
re-performed, can be continue,

00:00:43.529 --> 00:00:45.740
and what kind of roles that will take.

00:00:45.740 --> 00:00:46.428
It's really interesting

00:00:46.428 --> 00:00:48.764
to see how the performers can be present

00:00:48.764 --> 00:00:49.913
in the museum, live.

